<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - MANIFOLDS - VALVE COVER/INTAKE MANIFOLD - INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>INSTALLATION</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If valve cover/intake manifold gasket is not damaged and in good condition, it can be reused.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place gasket onto cylinder head.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place rubber oil deflectors (
                <emph type="bold">1, Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050310">3.10</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) onto the oil baffle plate.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>BE SURE OIL DEFLECTORS ARE SECURED TO THE OIL BAFFLE PLATE.</para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Check if breather element is placed in the oil baffle with the nylon mesh facing up (2, Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050310">3.10</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a generous bead of RTV sealant on the long right hand oil deflector (push rod side)
                from front to rear (
                <emph type="bold">4, Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050310">3.10</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1050309" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg2309" filename="../figeg2/eg2309.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 3.9.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Valve Cover/Intake Manifold</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Mounting Bolts</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050310" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg3562" filename="../figeg3/eg3562.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 3.10.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Rubber Oil Deflector</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Nylon Mesh</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Oil Baffle Plate</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. RTV Sealant</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If road draft tube was removed, install to valve cover/intake manifold as follows. (Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050311">3.11</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Lubricate and install a new O-Ring onto draft tube.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Holding valve/cover intake manifold above engine, insert draft tube into bore located on
                    the rear right hand side of the valve cover/intake manifold (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050311">3.11</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>THE DRAFT TUBE MUST BE INSTALLED INTO THE VALVE COVER/INTAKE MANIFOLD BEFORE THE VALVE
                            COVER IS LOWERED ONTO THE ENGINE.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>DO NOT ALLOW THE VALVE COVER/INTAKE MANIFOLD TO CONTACT THE RTV SEALANT APPLIED ON THE OIL
                            DEFLECTOR, UNTIL INSTALLATION. IF THE VALVE COVER/ INTAKE MANIFOLD IS LOWERED ONTO THE RTV
                            SEALANT AND THEN REMOVED, THE OIL DEFLECTOR WILL COME OFF THE OIL BAFFLE PLATE.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the valve cover/intake manifold (with road draft tube in place) onto the cylinder
                head.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>BE SURE THE VALVE COVER/INTAKE MANIFOLD AND GASKET ALIGN PROPERLY.</para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure valve cover/intake manifold to cylinder head using thirteen (13) mounting capscrews.
                Tighten to special torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install aneroid tube to valve cover/intake manifold as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove protective caps from aneroid elbow and valve cover/intake manifold port.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Attach aneroid tube nut to aneroid elbow. Tighten nut. Using new copper gaskets on the
                    hollow screw, attach aneroid tube valve cover/intake manifold. Tighten screw to special torque value
                    (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050312">3.12</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050311" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3563" filename="../figeg3/eg3563.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.11.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Intake Manifold</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Draft Tube O-Ring</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. RTV Sealant</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Oil Deflector</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. Oil Baffle</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. Breather</callout1>
                        <callout1>7. Road Draft Tube</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050312" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2699" filename="../figeg2/eg2699.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.12.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Aneroid</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Aneroid Elbow</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Aneroid Tube Nut</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Aneroid Tube</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. Hollow Screw And Gasket</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. Valve Cover/Intake Manifold</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
